00:06:24.100 --> 00:06:30.940
So for those of you that aren't in marketing or have data protection laws to deal with,

00:06:31.859 --> 00:06:41.339
GDPR is a law that was written in 2018 in Europe, essentially governing who can access

00:06:41.339 --> 00:06:49.100
your data, who can process it, where it's processed and a lot of other things, really

00:06:49.380 --> 00:06:55.779
putting the ownership of data back into where it honestly truly should belong, right?

00:06:55.779 --> 00:07:03.739
Like the data should belong to each individual and giving a bit more options to how you

00:07:03.739 --> 00:07:08.739
can allow companies or disallow companies to utilize your data.

00:07:09.299 --> 00:07:12.899
There's also US-based regulations.

00:07:12.899 --> 00:07:20.059
So there's the CCPA, so the California Agreement, essentially, which isn't as stringent

00:07:20.059 --> 00:07:23.739
as the GDPR, but it's kind of going into that direction.

00:07:24.019 --> 00:07:27.140
And I would certainly expect that there's more regulation coming.

00:07:27.700 --> 00:07:36.660
I know very recently there was a thing about, I guess, Facebook saying that they would

00:07:36.660 --> 00:07:37.619
pull out of Europe.

00:07:38.660 --> 00:07:41.380
I think that just happens in the last few days.

00:07:42.100 --> 00:07:46.660
And then the European foreign minister is saying like, OK, well, then do it.

00:07:47.660 --> 00:07:51.380
So I think there's a lot of back and forth that happens all the time.

00:07:52.859 --> 00:08:03.140
But to actually get to your actual question, so I feel like marketing companies or

00:08:03.140 --> 00:08:12.380
companies as a whole shouldn't necessarily try to figure out how to skirt those

00:08:12.380 --> 00:08:17.380
different things. But there's a lot of things that can be done to actually test your

00:08:17.380 --> 00:08:21.019
marketing initiatives without being sort of on the creepy marketing side.

00:08:22.339 --> 00:08:26.779
There is probabilistic marketing attribution, for example.

00:08:28.380 --> 00:08:32.179
A lot of the things that we've been doing internally is relying a lot more on testing and

00:08:32.179 --> 00:08:39.219
experimentation. So, you know, really interestingly, more traditional initiatives like

00:08:39.219 --> 00:08:45.260
building marketing mix models, for example, is probably going to become a little bit more

00:08:45.260 --> 00:08:52.500
invoking and because, you know, you aren't going to have that definitive click

00:08:52.500 --> 00:08:55.219
attribution that you are used to.

00:08:55.539 --> 00:09:01.419
We already see that if we look into channel attribution in different countries.

00:09:01.419 --> 00:09:08.140
So we operate globally and I can tell you that, you know, for US users, for example, we

00:09:08.140 --> 00:09:13.900
have a lot more insights into like their paths on our websites or, you know, what their

00:09:14.460 --> 00:09:18.340
different channel mixes are compared to someone like you that would be in the UK.

00:09:20.219 --> 00:09:30.380
But yeah, ultimately, from a company perspective, it's about offering the right thing to

00:09:30.380 --> 00:09:36.340
someone. And I think sometimes, especially on marketing, we've gone to the point where

00:09:36.340 --> 00:09:41.859
everything and I say this as a data person, everything is so measured that people have

00:09:41.859 --> 00:09:47.739
forgotten that really, truly marketing should be about just offering someone or offering a

00:09:47.739 --> 00:09:50.700
prospect the best possible customer experience.

00:09:50.900 --> 00:09:52.299
And that's really what it's about.

00:09:52.580 --> 00:09:56.940
And the idea, hopefully, is that with that comes revenue that's attached to it.

00:09:57.260 --> 00:10:02.900
And then from a data perspective, it becomes basically my problem to prove that, you know,

00:10:02.900 --> 00:10:09.979
there is a correlation between offering a good experience to actually having revenue

00:10:09.979 --> 00:10:16.059
driven into the company rather than saying like, hey, OK, we're going to, you know, we're

00:10:16.059 --> 00:10:21.619
going to cookie track everything because that's likely going to go away in the form that

00:10:21.619 --> 00:10:22.900
