So each of those different brands that we own, so, you know, CM Group, the company I work for,

00:14:55.859 --> 00:15:03.340
owns the namesake company Campaign Monitor, but also Sailthrough, Seligent, Emma, Cheetah and a few more.

00:15:04.539 --> 00:15:09.580
There is different levels of sophistication that we have in terms of data models for all of these

00:15:09.580 --> 00:15:18.059
different products. So the longer answer would be it depends on, you know, on which brand we're

00:15:18.059 --> 00:15:19.780
talking about here internally.

00:15:20.979 --> 00:15:29.820
But to generalize, I think on the marketing side, we are probably the most measured function in our

00:15:29.820 --> 00:15:35.059
company. We tend to track and over track everything we can track.

00:15:36.419 --> 00:15:45.380
And it's become the idea is really how can we find like those needles in the haystack to actually try

00:15:45.380 --> 00:15:47.619
to tell us what we should be looking into?

00:15:48.940 --> 00:15:53.900
And one of the and I mentioned that my team is kind of split into two groups.

00:15:53.900 --> 00:15:57.780
There's like a insights and reporting team and then there's advanced analytics team.

00:15:58.820 --> 00:16:04.419
One function inside of the advanced analytics team is like an automation practice where

00:16:04.419 --> 00:16:10.380
essentially we write a lot of code that deals with anomaly detection.

00:16:11.219 --> 00:16:19.299
And the idea behind that is if we have, I find a really bad metaphor, say like our data is the size

00:16:19.299 --> 00:16:20.739
of New York City, right?

00:16:21.059 --> 00:16:27.260
There is no way for us to actually look into that and kind of investigate the whole New York City.

00:16:27.619 --> 00:16:36.380
So through the automation anomaly detections that we write, we try to eliminate sort of like most

00:16:36.380 --> 00:16:42.419
of New York City and just tell us, OK, these are the specific houses that you should look into that

00:16:42.419 --> 00:16:43.900
have something unique going on.

00:16:44.260 --> 00:16:48.380
And then the insights and reporting function that I have would then actually go into these

00:16:48.380 --> 00:16:55.940
individual houses and search for a specific item in a different room that I hope that metaphor

00:16:55.940 --> 00:17:03.140
holds true. But essentially to answer that question, I think it's more of a question of how can we

00:17:03.140 --> 00:17:08.900
identify what is actually important out of like that large treasure trove of information rather than not

00:17:08.900 --> 00:17:10.739
having enough information to work with?

