Slack bot. So first of all, thank you for that.

00:17:28.619 --> 00:17:29.140
I love it.

00:17:29.619 --> 00:17:36.180
Yeah, I'm just wondering how the insight finding leads to business decisions.

00:17:36.180 --> 00:17:41.939
So I'm kind of trying to balance out the granularity of the information that I share and I'm

00:17:41.939 --> 00:17:43.979
wondering how that conversation goes within your team.

00:17:44.900 --> 00:17:46.339
OK, first of all, I love that.

00:17:46.339 --> 00:17:48.180
I love hearing everything about this.

00:17:48.540 --> 00:17:55.140
And we could probably talk another couple of hours about, you know, where I feel like business

00:17:55.140 --> 00:17:59.420
intelligence has a place in the business and where it does not.

00:17:59.699 --> 00:18:05.819
And what we found, again, we have this specific use case that my team is sitting on the

00:18:05.819 --> 00:18:12.619
marketing team. We're integrated into marketing and we have a lot of people that are the

00:18:12.619 --> 00:18:18.459
end users of or the stakeholders of our analyses that do not have like a quantitative

00:18:18.459 --> 00:18:23.900
background, right? Like you might be able to or you might have to do an analysis that has a

00:18:23.979 --> 00:18:28.060
regression in it and then explain it to a team of copywriters.

00:18:28.619 --> 00:18:31.900
That is a very unique thing that happens here all the time.

00:18:32.819 --> 00:18:36.979
And what we found and we have a, I would say, decent stack.

00:18:36.979 --> 00:18:42.739
So we have a Looker instance sitting on top of a Redshift instance that flows almost all of

00:18:42.739 --> 00:18:45.859
our data from a reporting perspective flows into that.

00:18:47.140 --> 00:18:52.140
But what we found is that building more and more and more business intelligence didn't

00:18:52.140 --> 00:18:59.939
really increase the knowledge or data data aptitude for our for the teams, because there

00:18:59.939 --> 00:19:04.819
is a hesitancy of utilizing those BI tools.

00:19:08.099 --> 00:19:12.020
You know, if you don't if you don't have like a data background.

00:19:12.380 --> 00:19:15.979
So instead, this is what what you're referencing there.

00:19:16.339 --> 00:19:18.619
So instead, we've actually kind of flipped it around.

00:19:18.619 --> 00:19:25.699
So we wrote this Slack bot that basically takes information, you know, in this case, like, you

00:19:25.699 --> 00:19:31.579
know, some anomaly with detection and then surfaces that information right to when it

00:19:31.579 --> 00:19:37.060
happens to people on Slack, just pinging them like, hey, something's going on in your area

00:19:37.900 --> 00:19:39.260
that you should be looking into.

00:19:39.579 --> 00:19:45.660
So with that process, we've been able to really kind of change of how people digest

